Math-Matrix-Banded

A banded matrix (or band matrix or band diagonal matrix) is a matrix
whose non-zero columns are confined to a diagonal band. Obviously,
such a structure allows for more efficient storage and computation
than for a general matrix.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Math::Matrix::Banded

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        https://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Math-Matrix-Banded

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Math-Matrix-Banded

    CPAN Ratings
        https://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Math-Matrix-Banded

    Search CPAN
        https://metacpan.org/release/Math-Matrix-Banded


